HEADWORD: capacitance
<hw>ca*pac"i*tance</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧*p⟦acr⟧s"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ait⟧ns)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an electrical phenomenon whereby an
electric charge is stored.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> electrical capacity, capacity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Electronics)</fld> <def>a measure of the ability of
a capacitor to store electrical charge; the ratio of the charge on one
plate of a capacitor to the potential difference between the
plates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capacitate</ent>⟦br⟧
